# Testing Strategy

## The test pyramid — enforce the ratio

```text
        E2E Tests (few, slow, catch integration regressions)
       /                                                    \
     Integration Tests (medium, real infra, per milestone)
    /                                                        \
  Unit Tests (many, fast, in-process, parallel, ≥ 85% coverage)
```

We do NOT test the same thing at multiple levels. Unit tests cover logic. Integration tests cover contracts. E2E tests cover user journeys.

## Test categories and tags

```go
// Unit tests — no build tag; run with `go test ./...`
// No external dependencies. Must be runnable offline.

//go:build integration
// Integration tests — run with `go test -tags=integration ./...`
// Require compose-test stack running.

//go:build e2e
// E2E tests — run with `go test -tags=e2e ./...`
// Require full local deployment.
```

```python
# Python — pytest marks
@pytest.mark.unit         # no infra required
@pytest.mark.integration  # requires testcontainers
@pytest.mark.e2e          # requires full stack
```

## Mandatory test types per code category

| Code category | Required test types |
|---|---|
| packages/* (Go) | Unit ≥ 90%, benchmark for hot paths |
| middleware/* (Go) | Unit (httptest) + integration |
| store/* (Go) | Integration (real Postgres), no unit with mocks |
| gRPC handler/* | Unit (connect test client) + integration |
| Python repository/* | Integration (testcontainers), no unit with mocks |
| Python service/* | Unit (mock repository) |
| React components | Unit (Vitest + Testing Library) |
| React pages | Integration (Playwright) |

## Do not mock what you can test for real

Database stores are tested with real Postgres (testcontainers), never with mocked DB interfaces. Mocking a database interface tests the mock, not the SQL.

```go
// WRONG — tests the mock, not the SQL
func TestAgentStore_Get(t *testing.T) {
    mockDB := &MockDB{}
    mockDB.On("QueryRow", ...).Return(mockRow)
    store := NewAgentStore(mockDB)
    // This tests that store calls QueryRow; it doesn't test the SQL is correct
}

// RIGHT — real Postgres in integration test; catches SQL errors, index issues, RLS
//go:build integration
func TestAgentStore_GetByIDAndOrg_CrossOrgReturnsNil(t *testing.T) {
    pool := testPGPool(t) // uses testcontainers
    store := NewAgentStore(pool)
    orgA, orgB := insertTestOrg(t, pool), insertTestOrg(t, pool)
    agent := insertTestAgent(t, pool, orgB)

    result, err := store.GetByIDAndOrg(t.Context(), agent.ID, orgA) // org A asking for org B's agent
    require.NoError(t, err)
    require.Nil(t, result) // must return nil, not an error
}
```

## Every security-critical path has a negative test

For every `PERMISSION_DENIED`, `401`, `403`, `AGENT_NOT_AUTHORIZED` response code: there must be a test that verifies the denial. Security tests are as important as functionality tests.

```go
// Test matrix for proxy auth:
// 1. Missing token → 401
// 2. Invalid token format → 401
// 3. Revoked token → 401
// 4. Expired token → 401
// 5. Valid token, wrong org agent → 403
// 6. Valid token, inactive agent → 403
// 7. Valid token, insufficient permissions → 403
// 8. Valid token, correct org, active agent → 200
```
